{"schemaVersion":1,"book":"RUT","entries":[{"id":"peshitta-notas-1095","title":"Rut 0:0–1","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":0,"verseStart":0,"chapterEnd":0,"verseEnd":1},"content":"<p lang=\"es-ES\" style=\"text-align:center;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-right:0pt;line-height:16pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:24pt;font-weight:bold;\">LIBRO DE</span></p><p lang=\"es-ES\" style=\"text-align:center;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-right:0pt;line-height:23pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:24pt;font-weight:bold;\">RUT</span></p><span style=\"\">Aram., </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\">Ketava d’Rot. </span><span style=\"\">Se traduce </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\">Libro de Rut. </span><span style=\"\">El nombre </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\">Rut </span><span style=\"\">significa </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\">amiga. </span><span style=\"\">Heb., </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\">Rut. </span><span style=\"\">De autor desconocido, la fecha de redacción se sitúa alrededor del año 1100 a. C. El tema central, aunque aparezca en la genealogía al final del libro, es el rey David, un descendiente directo de una moabita. La mención de Belén, la aldea donde nació Jesús; la genealogía de David, ascendiente directo del Señor; y el matrimonio entre un judío y una gentil, figura de la salvación para todos los pueblos, nos sugiere un mensaje claramente mesiánico, cuyo fin principal es Jesucristo el Señor. Este libro relata las circunstancias en que se casaron un israelita justo y una viuda moabita. Las condiciones ambientales e históricas prevalecientes en Judá fuerzan a su familia a residir en Moab, donde conoce casualmente a Boaz. En circunstancias aparentemente anómalas, contraen matrimonio, y el fruto de esa relación son los ascendientes directos del Señor. Desde un punto de vista natural, los acontecimientos narrados en el libro pudieron haber tomado otro curso, pero la intervención del Señor lleva al feliz final que trajo la oportunidad de bendición para todas las naciones, evidencia de que el Señor tiene el control de todo y lleva siempre a cabo su propósito.</span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1096","title":"Rut 1:1","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":1},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b7.2.16-19'>Jue 2:16-19</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1097","title":"Rut 1:2","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":2,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":2},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>1</sup></span> </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">Aram.</span>, </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">Naami</span>, </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">que se traduce </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">mi dulce </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">o </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">mi placentera</span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">.</span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1098","title":"Rut 1:4","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":4,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":4},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b40.1.5'>Mat 1:5</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1099","title":"Rut 1:6","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":6,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":6},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b26.20.40'>Eze 20:40</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b36.2.7'>Sof 2:7</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b38.12.7'>Zac 12:7</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1100","title":"Rut 1:16","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":16,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":16},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b20.17.17'>Pro 17:17</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b20.31.30'>Pro 31:30</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1101","title":"Rut 1:20","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":20,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":20},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>2</sup></span> </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">Es decir</span>, </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">amargada de alma</span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">.</span></p><span style=\"color:#0000FF;\"></span></p><span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>3</sup></span> </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">El nombre </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">El-Shaddai </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">está compuesto por el vocablo </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">El</span>, </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">común en las lenguas semíticas para referirse a la Deidad</span>, </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">y por </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">Shaddai</span>, </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">derivado de </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">shadad</span>, </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">que puede traducirse </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">fuerte</span>, </span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\">vigoroso. </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">Regularmente se traduce</span><span style=\"font-style:italic;\" lang=\"es-ES\"> Dios Todopoderoso.</span></p><span style=\"color:#0000FF;\"></span></p><span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b1.17.1'>Gén 17:1</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b1.35.11'>Gén 35:11</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b1.48.3'>Gén 48:3</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b2.6.3'>Éxo 6:3</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1104","title":"Rut 2:1","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":2,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":2,"verseEnd":1},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b13.2.11-12'>1Cr 2:11-12</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b40.1.5'>Mat 1:5</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b42.3.32'>Luc 3:32</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1105","title":"Rut 2:2","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":2,"verseStart":2,"chapterEnd":2,"verseEnd":2},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b3.19.9'>Lev 19:9</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b5.24.19'>Deu 24:19</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1106","title":"Rut 2:12","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":2,"verseStart":12,"chapterEnd":2,"verseEnd":12},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b19.17.8'>Sal 17:8</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b19.91.4'>Sal 91:4</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b40.23.37'>Mat 23:37</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1107","title":"Rut 2:19","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":2,"verseStart":19,"chapterEnd":2,"verseEnd":19},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b19.41.1'>Sal 41:1</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1108","title":"Rut 3:7","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":7,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":7},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>4</sup></span> </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">Acto simbólico mediante el cual una mujer se ponía bajo la cobertura y protección de un varón.</span></p></span></p><span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b10.13.28'>2Sa 13:28</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b17.1.10'>Est 1:10</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b19.104.15'>Sal 104:15</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1110","title":"Rut 3:9","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":9,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":9},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>5</sup></span> </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">Expresión común de una mujer para una petición de matrimonio</span>, </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">especialmente en caso de obligación de levirato. Ver </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\" lang=\"es-ES\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b5.25.5-10'>Deu 25:5-10</a></span><span style=\"color:#008000;\" lang=\"es-ES\"> </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">y </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\" lang=\"es-ES\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b26.16.8'>Eze 16:8</a></span>.</span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\"> No obstante</span>, </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">en este caso no era una aplicación estricta del levirato</span>, </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">sino una mezcla de éste con la tradición de la época.</span></p></span></p><span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b5.25.5'>Deu 25:5</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b40.22.24'>Mat 22:24</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1112","title":"Rut 3:11","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":11,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":11},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b20.12.4'>Pro 12:4</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b20.31.10'>Pro 31:10</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1113","title":"Rut 3:13","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":13,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":13},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b5.25.5'>Deu 25:5</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b40.22.24'>Mat 22:24</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1114","title":"Rut 3:14","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":14,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":14},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b45.14.16'>Rom 14:16</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b47.8.21'>2Co 8:21</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1115","title":"Rut 4:1","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":4,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":1},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b6.20.4'>Jos 20:4</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1116","title":"Rut 4:7","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":4,"verseStart":7,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":7},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b5.25.8-10'>Deu 25:8-10</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1117","title":"Rut 4:11","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":4,"verseStart":11,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":11},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b1.29.25-30'>Gén 29:25-30</a></span><span style=\"color:#008000;\">;</span></p><span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>b</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b20.14.1'>Pro 14:1</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1118","title":"Rut 4:12","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":4,"verseStart":12,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":12},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b13.2.4'>1Cr 2:4</a></span><span style=\"color:#008000;\">;</span></p><span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>b</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b1.46.12'>Gén 46:12</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b40.1.3'>Mat 1:3</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b42.3.33'>Luc 3:33</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1119","title":"Rut 4:17","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":4,"verseStart":17,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":17},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>a</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b13.2.12'>1Cr 2:12</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b40.1.5'>Mat 1:5</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b42.3.32'>Luc 3:32</a></span><span style=\"color:#008000;\">;</span></p><span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>b</sup></span> </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b9.17.12'>1Sa 17:12</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b23.11.1'>Isa 11:1</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b40.1.5'>Mat 1:5</a></span>; </span><span style=\"color:#008000;text-decoration:underline;\"><a class=\"bible\" href='#b42.3.32'>Luc 3:32</a></span></p></span></p>"},{"id":"peshitta-notas-1120","title":"Rut 4:18","author":"Instituto Cultural Álef y Tau, A.C.","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":4,"verseStart":18,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":18},"content":"<span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\"><sup>6</sup></span> </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">Clara alusión a la genealogía de Jesucristo. El relato de la ordinaria relación entre Boaz y Rut</span>, </span><span style=\"\" lang=\"es-ES\">nos muestra la evidente intervención de la Deidad eterna en el tiempo para sus extraordinarios propósitos futuros y eternos.</span></p></span></p><span style=\"color:#0000FF;font-weight:bold;